FBIS4-24503 "drchi104_v_94016" FBIS-CHI-94-104 Daily Report 28 May 1994 TAIWAN Trade Deficit With EU Widens Trade Deficit With EU Widens OW2805142394 Taipei CNA in English 1335 GMT 28 May 94 OW2805142394 Taipei CNA English BFN [By Liu Kun-yuan and Danielle Yang] [Text] Madrid, May 27 (CNA) -- Taiwan registered its first four-monthly deficit ever with the European Union through April, according to customs statistics. The trade deficit of US$40 million resulted from increasing imports from and decreasing exports to the EU, customs officials said. Taiwan registered a US$543 million trade surplus with the EU in the first four months of 1993. During the January-April period, Taiwan imported US$3.596 billion worth of products from the EU, a growth of 8.7 percent from the first four months of last year. Taiwan's exports to the area totaled only US$3.556 billion, a 7.7 percent decline, the statistics showed. The US$7.153 billion in two-way trade between the two was a 0.1 percent decline.
